# FOUNDATION Fieldbus HSE (IEC 61158) over TCP port 1090 — an FDA (Field Device Access) message.
# The FDA message has no record/length prefix over TCP (unlike Kerberos/SunRPC); Message Length is the
# sole delimiter, so the on-wire FDA layout is identical to the UDP case.
# FDA Message Header (12 bytes): version 1, options 0x00, protocol-id-and-type 0x88, service 0x04,
# FDA address 0x00000001, message length 20 (12-byte header + 8-byte service body).
# source: constructed spec-accurate frame (FF-588 §6.3 / Wireshark 'ff' dissector layout). eth/ipv4/tcp
# envelope assembled by the netkitty encoder (valid IPv4 + TCP checksums); tshark frame.protocols =
# eth:ethertype:ip:tcp:ff (ff.hdr.ver=1, ff.hdr.len=20).
# bytes: [0:14] eth, [14:34] ipv4, [34:54] tcp(src 49152 dst 1090), [54:66] FDA header, [66:74] body.
